	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Aug 19th 11:07 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=168912><span id=Guru>Takanit</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>117 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.80]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have to disagree here. People think that the speed of your weapons must be the lowest to taunt better, that is correct in a way, yet incorrect in another.<br><br>It is true that fast weapons handle aggro pretty well, but that is because of the DAMAGE OUTPUT, not the delay of your weapon. Pre-28 the weapons with the best ratio will taunt better, then goes the damage bonus at 28 which isn't so much of a deal since it is only one. I saw a Warrior with Wurmy and Centi LS and he was keeping aggro from another Warrior with two Lammys. Why ? Because Lammys aren't as good as Wurmslayer without good damage bonus (40 - 45+.)<br><br>So I say stick with the Wurmy until you can get a better weapon. Lammy IS better, but only at higher levels.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=408258 target=_new>Hakthek Boilingfury ( Dwarven Paladin )</a> <br><b><span style='color: red;'>Brell Serilis<b></td></td></tr>
